ont id="limegreen"> - no they didn't just laugh out loud, but might have recognized what you said as a vague attempt at humor<br /><font color="limegreen">"lmao"</font id="limegreen"> - they definitely understand what you said was meant to be funny and are being nice<br /><font color="limegreen">"rofl"</font id="limegreen"> - they really aren't rolling on the floor, but possibly smiled<br /><font color="limegreen">"haha"</font id="limegreen"> - they are definitely laughing, more likely at you than with you<br /><font color="limegreen">"hahaha"</font id="limegreen"> - they found it funny<br /><font color="limegreen">"omfg will u plz stfu idiot" </font id="limegreen"> - dont let them fool you, this means they really found it incredibly funny and would like nothing better than for you to keep going<br /><br /><font color="red">Notes:</font id="red"><br /><br /><font color="limegreen">capitalization </font id="limegreen"> - ie HEHE or ROFL, consider this one level higher on the pecking order<br /><font color="limegreen">combos</font id="limegreen"> - ie "rofl lmao" are very complicated responses. You should definitely <font color="red">/shout Cool that was pretty funny what I said huh?</font id="red"> to get more info<br /><br /><br /></span></font></td>
